When I was a little kiddo (like 6 years old I think), I struggled with the concept of destiny a lot. I made a simple experiment: I climbed on top of the table and thought to myself: "I can jump down or not jump down. But if I decide to jump down, that was my destiny. And if I ...

... decide not to jump, then THAT was my destiny."

Finally, I decided to jump down, and then realized that the jumping was my destiny.

I could do whatever I wanted and it would be my destiny once it was done. I decided that destiny exists only in the past and future, never now.
